    <dialogue>
        <line>
            (You are standing on the eastern wall near the Grizedale guild complex. There are two Grizedale
            guards on patrol, who are barely awake.)
        </line>
        <line from="You">
            What is happening over there? That can't possibly be... WAKE UP you lazy good-for-nothings!!
        </line>
        <line from="Grizedale Guard 1">
            ............
        </line>
        <line from="Grizedale Guard 1">
            Huh..... what's the problem?
        </line>
        <line from="You">
            Are you blind, look over the wall, I better tell the supreme master!
        </line>
        <line>
            (You run to the Cartmel grand hall, the Grizedale guards fall asleep again)
        </line>
        <line from="Cartmel's Supreme Master">
            Ah yes, our brightest and most talented student. What is it?
        </line>
        <line from="You">
            I don't believe it myself. The grass over the wall has changed colour. We need to inform the rest of
            the guilds. They are coming back!
        </line>
        <line from="Cartmel's Supreme Master">
            Hmm. This is worrying. Our town is not ready for battle. Our guilds are uncooperative. Our troops
            are not prepared. The Hero of Lancaster is no longer alive, and I think it is time for someone
            to take the mantle.
        </line>
        <line from="Cartmel's Supreme Master">
            I need you to go to each guild and learn their way. Whether you are prepared or not, you will
            need to become the new Hero of Lancaster.
        </line>
        <line from="You">
            I will do what I must to protect us. Let me try the Cartmel test... let me earn the Wings of
            Cartmel!
        </line>
        <line from="Cartmel's Supreme Master">
            You may. But be cautious, there may be White Rose Clan scouts in the area...
        </line>
    </dialogue>
